# Testing Requirements

## When modifying business logic

Any change to these files MUST have corresponding test coverage:

- `src/lib/raidClassifier.ts` — raid classification logic
- `src/lib/upgradeEngine.ts` — upgrade filtering and scoring
- `src/lib/parseStatsBlock.ts` — item stat parsing

If a bug fix touches these files, add a regression test that would FAIL without the fix before applying it.

Tests live in `src/lib/__tests__/` and use vitest.

## Before committing

Always run `npm test` and verify all tests pass before creating any git commit. If tests fail, fix the issue before committing.

## Test patterns

- Test specific items/scenarios that caused bugs (e.g., "Hammer of Battle" mob name normalization)
- Test boundary conditions (empty arrays vs null, mixed raid/non-raid quest lists)
- Test that hybrid zones (Nagafen's Lair, Permafrost, Western Wastes, Dragon Necropolis, Icewell Keep) are NOT in RAID_ZONES
- Test that the upgrade count only counts items scoring above the current equipped item

## Raid classifier golden set (MANDATORY)

`src/lib/__tests__/raidClassifier.golden.test.ts` contains a curated set of real items from `item-database.json` with their exact data fields and expected raid/non-raid classification.

**When fixing a raid classification bug:**

1. Find the misclassified item in `item-database.json` (grep for its exact name)
2. Copy its `dropsfrom`, `dropmobs`, `relatedquests`, and `statsBlock` fields
3. Add the item to `MUST_BE_RAID` or `MUST_NOT_BE_RAID` in the golden set test file
4. Verify the new test FAILS before applying the fix (proves the test catches the bug)
5. Apply the fix and verify all golden set tests pass

**When modifying `raidClassifier.ts` for any reason:**

- Run `npm test` — the golden set will catch any regressions across all detection paths (zone, NPC, quest, relatedquests NPC scan, stat-twin)
- If a golden set test fails, the classifier change broke an existing classification — fix it before committing
- NEVER remove a golden set item to make tests pass; instead fix the classifier logic
